Any folders inside the  etc/skel/ directory will get copied into the user's home folder on install.
with root user structure such as
/etc/skel/Desktop
/etc/skel/Downloads
/etc/skel/Appimages
/etc/skel/Icons
/etc/skel/.local
/etc/skel/.local/share/plasma/
/etc/skel/.local/share/user-places.xbel
/etc/skel/.local/share/color-schemes/
/etc/skel/.config/plasma-org.kde.plasma.desktop-appletsrc * Panels etc stored here
/etc/skel/.local/share/konsole/ ~ profiles
/etc/skel/.conky
/usr/share/sddm/themes/ ~ login screens
/opt ~ can be used to store folders such as: shellscripts,icons, etc
usr/share/plasma/wallpapers/wallpapers/ ?konsole bgds

*
Restore theme settings and customizations
sudo apt-get install python3-pip
python3 -m pip install konsave
?post install script
